Here is the simple python code to call myy chatgpt:
from openai import OpenAI

client = OpenAI(
    api_key = &#39;xxxxxx&#39;,
)

def chat_gpt(prompt):
    response = client.chat.completions.create(
        model=&quot;gpt-3.5-turbo-0613&quot;,
        messages=[{&quot;role&quot;: &quot;user&quot;, &quot;content&quot;: prompt}]
    )
    return response.choices[0].message.content.strip()

There are the same meaning in English and Chinese:
世界上最大的机场 == the largest airport in the world
Why get total different facts  in two language with same meaning?
&gt;&gt;&gt; chat_gpt(&#39;世界上最大的机场&#39;)
&#39;世界上最大的机场是位于中国北京的北京大兴国际机场，其总占地面积达到47万平方米，跨度宽度1.4公里，是一座新建的现代化综合性机场。机场拥有七条跑道和四个航站楼，并且还具备了大规模机库和停机坪。这座机场于2019年9月正式投入使用。&#39;
&gt;&gt;&gt; chat_gpt(&#39;the largest airport in the world&#39;)
&#39;The King Fahd International Airport in Dammam, Saudi Arabia, is considered the largest airport in the world by area, covering 780 square kilometers (301 square miles).&#39;
